            <section class="copy" data-chapter-top="5" data-chapter-bottom="5">
                <div>
                    <aside class="mm-sidebar">
                        <div class="mm-side-graphic">
                            <div class="img-container"><img src="http://www.gq.com/static/long-form/images/0.7.23/pages/nicolas_cage/side_graphic/1.png" alt="Because he named his kid Kal-El" height="341" width="205">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </aside>
                    <header>
                        <h3>Because He’s Got a Sense of Humor About Himself</h3>
                    </header>
                    <p>When Cage crashed Andy Samberg's acting-seminar sketch "Get in the Cage" in 2012, you could <i>feel</i> the <i>SNL</i> cast's sheer ecstasy. "Probably one of my favorite five-minute periods ever on <i>SNL,</i>" says Seth Meyers. "I think it was one of Andy's happiest days," adds Bobby Moynihan. But the true winner was Cage: "I think people forget what good comic timing he has," says Moynihan. As Andy-Nic would say, "THAT'S HIGH PRAISE!" —<em>Sarah Ball</em>
                    </p>
                    <p class="video-wrapper">
                        <iframe width="640" height="360" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" src="https://screen.yahoo.com/weekend-cage-000000391.html?format=embed" allowfullscreen="true" mozallowfullscreen="true" webkitallowfullscreen="true" allowtransparency="true"></iframe>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="copy" data-chapter-top="6" data-chapter-bottom="6">
                <div>
                    <header>
                        <h3>Because Only a Gypsy Soul Could Make These Career Choices</h3>
                    </header>
                    <p>Cage's spiritual compass has always been a little haywire. First he was Catholic. Then he dabbled in voodoo. There was a sewing-talismans-into-his-clothes phase. But whatever powers he's mainlining from the Illuminati-tinged occult, they can be yours! Use our Cage-y tarot cards to guide your journey. —<em>Sarah Ball</em>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="cm-unit" style="">
                    <a href="https://subscribe.gq.com/subscribe/gq/88782?source=InArticleTout_Oct14_NicolasCageNationalTreasure"><img class="cm-image" src="http://www.gq.com/static/long-form/images/0.7.23/pages/nicolas_cage/cm/cm_desktop.png" alt="Subscribe to GQ.com">
                    </a>
                </div>
            </section>
